body:
This is a breaking change.

It refactors the `OwnedStream` API to try untangle some of the concepts in there by following a similar naming convention to `RefCell`. We now have:

```rust
mod value {
    pub trait Value;

    pub use crate::stream::RefMutStream as Stream;
}

mod stream {
    pub trait Stream;

    pub struct OwnedStream<S: Stream>;

    impl<S: Stream> OwnedStream<S> {
        pub fn borrow_mut(&mut self) -> RefMutStream;
    }

    pub struct RefMutStream<'a>;
}
```

So that there's now a clear link between the `Stream` you pass to `Value::stream` and the `OwnedStream` you might stash away on your own type.

The signature of `Value::stream` still takes its stream as `&mut Stream` rather than by value to keep things simple for callers.

I've also removed items marked as deprecated.
